                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12744436" author="thetaphi" created="Tue, 18 Aug 2009 10:37:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is, that the HTML parser strips all tags, that are not in SAFE_ELEMENTS. &amp;lt;TABLE&amp;gt; tags are replaced by &amp;lt;P&amp;gt; and all inner tags simply ignored and not passed through. As all other ContentHandlers (like OOXML, OpenXML,..) produce XHTML table tags, the HTML parser should preserve the table. This can be achieved by modifying the SAFE_ELEMENTS map.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you then convert the output to text-only, the output will contain tabs and NLs, as XHTMLContentHandler adds ignorableWhiteSpace between table tags and newlines after HTML block tags.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12746497" author="jukkaz" created="Sat, 22 Aug 2009 21:42:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in revision 806887 based on Uwe&apos;s suggestion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
